main event: Multiple unidentified objects were tracked on radar at Kirksville Air Force Station in Missouri on September 8, 1960.
interesting points: The objects appeared as well-defined targets about twice the size of a normal aircraft on the radar.
The objects approached the station at a high rate of speed, closing from 20 miles to 3 miles in a matter of seconds.
The objects exhibited no normal aircraft maneuverability, such as turns, climbs, or dives.
The objects disappeared from the radar scope rapidly after passing the station, indicating a high rate of speed.
No visual sightings of the objects were reported.
witnesses: Radar Approach Control Officer and other personnel at Kirksville Air Force Station
